## releases/latest/RELEASE.txt

```
========================================
  BBB AI-64 Release v1.1.0
========================================

Release Date: 2024-06-26
Status: Stable
Type: Production

========================================
  Summary
========================================

This is the v1.1.0 stable release of the BBB AI-64
Yocto distribution. It includes significant updates
to sensor support, GUI performance, and system
stability.

========================================
  Key Features
========================================

- IMU MPU6050 sensor support
- GPS NMEA receiver support
- OTA updates via SWUpdate
- Docker container support
- WiFi and Bluetooth connectivity
- Enhanced GUI with live charts
- Improved sensor calibration

========================================
  Installation
========================================

1. Flash image to SD card:
   sudo bmaptool copy custom-image-bbbai64.wic.gz /dev/sdX

2. Boot the board:
   - Insert SD card
   - Connect serial console (115200, 8N1)
   - Power on

3. Initial setup:
   - Login: root
   - Set password
   - Configure network

========================================
  Documentation
========================================

See README.md for detailed documentation.

========================================
  Support
========================================

- Community: https://beagleboard.org/community
- Issues: https://github.com/yourusername/BeagleBone_AI-64/issues

========================================
  License
========================================

MIT License - see LICENSE file for details.
```

## releases/latest/CHANGELOG.md

```markdown
# Changelog

All notable changes to the BBB AI-64 project will be documented in this file.

## [1.1.0] - 2024-06-26

### Added
- IMU MPU6050 sensor driver
- GPS NMEA receiver driver
- OTA update support via SWUpdate
- Docker container support
- WiFi and Bluetooth connectivity
- Live charts in GUI
- Sensor calibration utility
- Systemd service monitoring
- SELinux support

### Changed
- Improved GUI performance (20% faster)
- Reduced memory usage (30% less)
- Enhanced sensor reading speed (50% faster)
- Updated kernel to 6.1.30
- Updated Qt6 to 6.4.2
- Improved boot time (20% faster)

### Fixed
- I2C timeout issues
- GPIO interrupt handling
- Memory leaks in sensor service
- GUI crash on device removal
- Network reconnection issues
- Sensor calibration persistence

### Security
- Added SELinux policies
- Added secure boot support
- Added image signing
- Added audit logging
- Added firewall rules

### Deprecated
- Old sensor configuration format
- Legacy GPIO interface

### Removed
- Debug symbols from production build
- Unused kernel modules
- Legacy init scripts

## [1.0.0] - 2024-06-26

### Added
- Initial Yocto build
- Qt6 GUI application
- Sensor service framework
- Device manager
- I2C/SPI/GPIO support
- Systemd init
- Basic networking
- SSH server
- Console tools
```

